  "title": "Nvidia Q1 2025 Earnings Call",
  "datetime": "2025-05-28T20:00:00Z",
  "period": "CY2025_Q1",
  "location": "Santa Clara, CA",
  "url": "https://investor.nvidia.com/",
  "turns": [
    {
      "speaker_id": "jensen-huang",
      "speaker_name": "Jensen Huang",
      "speaker_role": "CEO",
      "timestamp": "00:01:00",
      "text": "Blackwell is in full production and demand continues to exceed our ability to supply. Data center revenue was $39.1 billion, up 73% year-over-year. We shipped over 70,000 GB200 NVL72 rack-scale systems in the quarter — each one a $3 million AI supercomputer. Sovereign AI is becoming a major demand driver: 40 countries are now building national AI infrastructure on our platform. Inference workloads are growing faster than training, which is net positive for our volumes as inference requires continuous compute capacity."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "colette-kress",
      "speaker_name": "Colette Kress",
      "speaker_role": "CFO",
      "timestamp": "00:18:00",
      "text": "Total revenue was $44.1 billion, up 69% year-over-year. Gross margin was 73.5%. Operating income was $29.9 billion. We generated $26.1 billion in free cash flow. For Q2, we expect revenue of $45 billion, plus or minus 2%, with gross margin of approximately 73.5%."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "operator",
      "speaker_name": "Operator",
      "speaker_role": "Operator",
      "timestamp": "00:38:00",
      "text": "Our next question comes from Ben Reitzes at Melius Research."
    },
    {
      "speaker_id": "analyst-ben-reitzes",
      "speaker_name": "Ben Reitzes",
      "speaker_role": "Analyst",
      "timestamp": "00:38:20",
      "text": "Jensen, 40 sovereign AI countries — can you frame what the average deal size looks like versus hyperscaler deals, and how you think about the government customer concentration risk?"
    }
  ],
